==Description==
'''Minerva''', referred to as "Mother" by wanderers, is a sentient, omniscient entity native to '''Level 483''' and its sub-levels. It is described as a tall, lanky pitch-black figure - originally presumed to be a sub-class of the [[Entity 6|Dullers]], recent information has surfaced disproving this: 
* The lack of a need to hunt, or otherwise consume organic matter;
* A lack of bodily organs, being pitch-black and amorphous;
* And a relatively isolated demeanor, partly due to the conditions of '''Level 483'''.
Due to these newly discovered properties about Entity 61, it has been designated its own slot.

As aforementioned, '''Minerva''' has a notable lack of bodily organs. They have an amorphous body, being able to shift and bend it to their will. Despite having amorphous and inconstant features, they almost always assume the form of a lanky humanoid, with four fingers as opposed to five. Due to the entity's shapeshifting abilities, it is possible for it to fit into small, cramped spaces and claustrophobic areas. 

As opposed to hunting wanderers for sport or otherwise to hunt, they choose to observe wanderers from a distance. For inexplicable reasons, encounters with '''Minerva''' almost always result in one contracting a form of amnesia upon exiting the level, coupled with severe paranoia and anxiety. Despite these negative effects it exhibits, '''Minerva''' is relatively passive unless provoked. It gets agitated by loud and startling noises - it also gets provoked by insults, being able to understand most human languages, save for [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extinct_language dead languages]. 

Encounters with '''Mother''' are inconstant, appearing for mere minutes at most before fading away. Encounters with it prove that, despite easily getting agitated, it lacks the physical strength and physique to properly inflict harm on a person. 

Much like how photographs are altered in [[Level 12]], attempting to photograph '''Mother''' results in arbitrary colors and patterns. Upon further research, these images exert psychedelic and hazardous mental properties on wanderers. Due to this, the image has been expunged for viewing convenience. 

